os.environ['HTTPS_PROXY']= '10.10.78.61:3128'
!'sentinel/dhusget.sh' \
-d 'https://s5phub.copernicus.eu/dhus/' \
-u 's5pguest' -p 's5pguest' \
-m 'Sentinel-5' \
-S 2020-11-01T00:00:00.000Z -E 2020-11-30T20:00:00.000Z \
-F 'platformname:Sentinel-5 AND producttype:L2__NO2___ AND processinglevel:L2 AND processingmode:Offline' \
-l 100 \
-c 68.14712,7.798000:97.34466,38.090000 \
-o 'product'

fig=plt.figure(figsize=(40,15)) # create a figure frame and set up the figure size
ax = plt.axes(projection=ccrs.PlateCarree()) # Creates an empty subplot 
# Plot VarNO2 where we remove the time dimension `VarNO2[0]`
extent = [60,100,0,40]
VarNO2[0].plot.pcolormesh(ax=ax, x='longitude', y='latitude', \
                          add_colorbar=True, cmap='seismic', \
                           transform=ccrs.PlateCarree(),vmin=0,vmax=0.0005) 
ax.set_extent(extent)
ax.add_feature(cartopy.feature.RIVERS) # add river
ax.set_title('S-5p L2 NO$_2$ ({}) '.format(str(date[0]))) # add title
ax.coastlines('10m')  # add coastline
ax.stock_img() # add the color of earth
ax.gridlines()  # add grid line
